
[1]christendom

   CHRISTENDOM, n.

   1. The territories, countries or regions inhabited by Christians, or
   those who profess to believe in the Christian religion.

   2. The whole body of Christians.

   3. Christianity; the Christian religion; as, while Christendom
   prevailed.
